transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hey, John, I just ordered and I got my pill and I picked the A-G version and I just wanted to make sure that's what was sent out to me.

Speaker 1: Okay. If there was a mistake, we'll get it fixed, but let's get this checked out.

Speaker 2: Your name and zip code?

Speaker 1: Micah, M-I-C-A-H, Scott, last name, 30214.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Because I'm showing on your commercials it has A-G-V on the pill.

Speaker 2: Right, it does show that on the ad, but that's not even actually how the A-G-V pill looks.

Speaker 1: But I will ask you to take out a pill.

Speaker 2: You're on Wallace Street, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's correct.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Can you tell me what's stamped on the pill?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: If it was a mistake, I'm going to get it fixed for you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, and then I ordered two of them and one came.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you stamped on – Oh, go ahead.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: A-C-3-4-0.

Speaker 2: Okay, so that is the wrong pill.

Speaker 1: You were right there.

Speaker 2: It should have just said 100, so if you told me 100, then that would have been the A-G-V pill.

Speaker 1: That's what the ad looks like, but the actual A-G-V one, like I said, will just have 100 stamped on it.

Speaker 2: So I'll get this replaced for you.

Speaker 1: And then regarding what you were talking about a second ago, what you did was you bought 10 and then added 10 extra pills.

Speaker 2: They all came in that same bottle.

Speaker 1: So this will all be in the bottle.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: That makes sense.

Speaker 1: That makes sense.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: So I'm getting it fixed for you, Mike.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry about that.

Speaker 1: But you'll get 20 of the right ones.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: So 100 is what's coming.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: So what did I get?

Speaker 1: You got just regular generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: So it's safe.

Speaker 1: It's just not the enhanced one you wanted.

Speaker 2: So we sell both.

Speaker 1: That's how the mix-up happens.

Speaker 2: Somewhere along the road, it got mixed up and then sent out to you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So I'll just expect that in how long?

Speaker 2: In a few days.

Speaker 1: I'm having a pharmacy send it out as soon as possible.

Speaker 2: I just sent them a message about it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Well, thanks a lot.

Speaker 2: Of course, sir.

Speaker 1: Have a good night.
